# Component Guidelines

## File Structure

```
components/
├── ComponentName/
│   └── index.tsx      # Main component export
templates/
├── PageTemplate/
│   ├── index.tsx      # Page composition
│   └── Section/
│       └── index.tsx  # Page section
```

## Component Conventions

### Naming
- PascalCase for component names
- Folder name matches component name
- Export from `index.tsx`

### Props
- Use TypeScript interfaces
- Destructure props in function signature
- Use `className` for style overrides

### Example Component

```tsx
interface CardProps {
  title: string;
  description?: string;
  className?: string;
  children?: React.ReactNode;
}

export function Card({ title, description, className, children }: CardProps) {
  return (
    <div className={cn("rounded-lg border border-n-5 p-6", className)}>
      <h3 className="h5 mb-2">{title}</h3>
      {description && <p className="body-2 text-n-3">{description}</p>}
      {children}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Styling Guidelines

### Use Tailwind Classes
- Prefer Tailwind utilities over custom CSS
- Use design system classes: `.h1`, `.body-1`, etc.
- Compose with `classnames` or `cn` utility

### Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach
- Breakpoints: `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`
- Test on all breakpoints

### Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Add `aria-*` attributes when needed
- Ensure keyboard navigation works
- Maintain color contrast ratios

## Import Patterns

```tsx
// External dependencies
import { useState } from "react";
import classnames from "classnames";

// Internal components
import { Button } from "@/components/Button";

// Types
import type { SectionProps } from "./types";
```
